OL,3,CLabour Government accused of
OL,4,C'betraying' Troubles victims
OL,6,F"Has the Government not put us through
OL,7,Fenough, 27 years I have been fighting,
OL,8,Fand I'm two steps forward and 27 back,
OL,9,FI've had enough, I'm tired of having
OL,10,Fto fight, I want my rights and I want
OL,11,Fthem as soon as possible.
OL,13,F"The Secretary of State has turned his
OL,14,Fback on us.
OL,16,F"A year ago the Secretary of State
OL,17,Fstood up and said he was against the
OL,18,FLegacy Act, and now he is doing
OL,19,Fexactly the same.
