OL,4,C'betraying' Troubles victims
OL,6,F"We're not going to stand for it,
OL,7,Fwe're here for an inquest and we're
OL,8,Fnot going to stop until we get one."
OL,10,FGrainne Teggart, from Amnesty, said
OL,11,Fseeking to appeal the judgment "raises
OL,12,Fvery significant questions about the
OL,13,FUK Government's commitment to their
OL,14,Fown promise to repeal and replace the
OL,15,FAct".
OL,17,F"The decision is a betrayal of the UK
OL,18,FGovernment's commitments and fails
OL,19,Fvictims who expected repeal to mean
OL,20,Frepeal," she said.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@dO]sD@`OUwD@DO]yD@AOU|D@HO]
